\label{lem:circum}
	Let $X=\{x_0,\dots,x_d\}$ and $Y=\{y_0,\dots,y_d\}$ be subsets of $\mathbb R^d$ in general position such that every pair of points in $X\times Y$ determines a unique distance. Suppose that for every $i$
	\begin{equation*}
		\left\lVert #1 \right\rVert{y_i-x_i}<\left\lVert #1 \right\rVert{y_i-x_{i+1}}<\dots<\left\lVert #1 \right\rVert{y_i-x_{i-1}},
	\end{equation*}
	where the indices are taken mod $d+1$. Then $O(X)$ is in the interior of $conv(Y)$.

